Class Time

  • java.lang.Object
    • Time
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Cloneable, java.lang.Comparable<Time>
    public class Time
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Cloneable, java.lang.Comparable<Time>
    This class defines the Time object, which is displayed in HH:MM AM/PM format and which can be mutated to and from a String object. Time can also be "shifted" by a given number of minutes, as well as compared to other Time objects.
